Given a singly linked list node, and an integer k, reverse every k contiguous group of nodes.

Constraints

n â‰¤ 100,000 where n is the number of nodes in node

Example:-1
Input:
node = 0->1->2->3
k = 2

Output
1->0->3->2

Example:-2
Input:
node= 0->1->2->3
k = 3
Output
2->1->0->3


C++ code:
LLNode* solve(LLNode* node, int k) {
    if(!node) return node;
    LLNode* prev = NULL;
    auto cur = node;
    int l = k;
    while(cur&&l--){
        auto temp = cur->next;
        temp = cur->next;
        cur->next = prev;
        prev = cur;
        cur = temp;
    }
    node->next = cur;
    node->next = solve(cur,k);
    return prev;
}
